---
// One-Tap Injection Fax — Manual (write / walk / print) vs Automated (one tap).
// Ported faithfully from his design handoff "Manual vs One-Tap.standalone.html":
// markup is the authored scene verbatim, the DCLogic `Component` class is reproduced
// as a plain class (element lookups scoped to the component root, the {{ start }}/
// {{ reset }} bindings replaced with data-attrs, auto-run on scroll-into-view, and a
// scale-to-fit so the whole stage is visible in the pinned viewport). All motion lives
// in SVG user-space, so a single CSS transform on the scene is safe (no rect math).
// Text tailored to the real clinic: Tri-City Eye Care injection orders, same patient
// "Carl Shen" as the biometry race for continuity. Patients are fictional.
---
<div class="bench-scene" data-bench-scene>
<div id="scene-root" class="onetap-scene" style="width:1200px;margin:0 auto;padding:24px 30px 28px;font-family:'IBM Plex Sans',sans-serif;color:#E6E8EC;background:#131418;">

  <!-- HEADER -->
